  "title": "driver",
  "description": "<p>Roles & Responsibilities</p><p>Delivery drivers have a variety of duties in addition to driving their routes and making their deliveries. Other</p><p>important responsibilities include:</p><p>- Following the best practices for safety, both on the road and while loading or unloading a truck</p><p>- Maintains communication with management to be informed of any change of delivery, route, or schedule</p><p>- Communicating with dispatchers, drivers, and other team members to make deliveries</p><p>- Communicate with customers by phone to update them of the time of deliveries if there have been issues or changes to their estimated time of arrival</p><p>- Meeting delivery deadlines</p><p>- Performing basic truck maintenance</p><p>- Loading and unloading</p><p>- Obtaining client or customer signatures when needed</p><p>- If not follow the basic driving rules and made accident or fine means, driver must be the responsibilty</p><p>- daily drop points 20 to 25 location,driving 14feet freezer lorry</p><p>- loading area jurong</p>",
